Roosevelt High School
April 30 at 2:09 PM ¬∑

Right now, we do not know what Graduation will look like. We are waiting to see how Covid-19 progresses. We would like to, however, save a date for our Graduation. We will do our best to hold Graduation on the evening of June 24th. At this time we are not sure of the format or location of the event, but we are looking at many different options.

Please save this date on your calendar and stay tuned for more information.

post_text:
Today is International Social Emotional Learning Day!

Social and emotional learning, often known as SEL, is the process that helps kids learn critical skills, attitudes, and mindsets for social and emotional success. These skills cover five major areas: self-awareness, self-management, social awareness, relationships, and responsible decision-making. It‚Äôs actually difficult to describe in just one sentence because SEL covers everything from building confidence and managing emotions to making friends and understanding ethical decision-making skills. These are truly the foundational skills that help kids to be successful in and out of school. The link has some free resources that you may use.

https://www.thepathway2success.com/free-social-emotional-learning-resources/

Dear WPS family,
It is with sadness that I say we likely won‚Äôt have enough bagged breakfasts and lunches tomorrow. Southgate and Lincoln Park ran out 15 minutes within opening. We are trying to get more food but there is no way the trucks can bring it by tomorrow. We will continue to try and keep you posted. That means at 11am tomorrow we will begin to hand out food, until it is gone. We have 800 bags prepared. We know for next week to increase this by a factor of 3. I am so sorry. No one knew it would be in this much demand. Please be patient as we adapt our plans.

Dr. Cost

post_text: Tonight, the police alerted us to a post on social media that was threatening in nature to the students at Wilson Middle School. An officer is at the student‚Äôs home and is investigating the credibility of the threat. The student will not be at school tomorrow. An increased police presence will be at Wilson tomorrow morning to reassure students and parents we are taking this seriously and the student will not be on school property. Please let the police investigate and withhold speculation on social media and talk with your child about the seriousness of making any type of threats. We will email you tomorrow as we know more details, but school will be in session Friday, May 25, 2018.

Wages and benefits per WEA master agreement.
